  "title": "Therapist Aide",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><p>· Perform a variety of beauty treatments and facials, based on client preferences and requirements.</p><p>· Conduct thorough consultations with clients to understand their specific needs, concerns, and desired outcomes, and recommend suitable treatments accordingly.</p><p>· Stay updated on the latest industry trends.</p><p>· Advise clients on skincare routines, post-treatment care, and recommend appropriate retail products for home use to enhance treatment results.</p><p>· Build and maintain a loyal clientele base by fostering strong relationships and delivering personalized experiences that exceed customer expectations.</p><p>· Comply with all health and safety regulations, including proper handling and disposal of products, adhering to sanitation protocols, and using personal protective equipment when necessary.</p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p>· Proven work experience as a Beautician or similar role.</p><p>· Knowledge of various beauty treatments, techniques, and products.</p><p>· Proficient in performing facials and other relevant beauty services.</p><p>· Excellent interpersonal and communication skills, with the ability to listen to client needs and provide appropriate recommendations.</p><p>· Ability to multitask and work efficiently in a fast-paced environment.</p><p><strong>Flexibility to work evenings, weekends, and holidays as needed.</strong></p><p>We thank you for your interest and we regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified. All resumes received will be used for recruitment purposes only.</p><p>EA License ID: 18C9520</p><p>EA Registration ID: R1765753</p>",
